  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Capacity Development Programme: Inclusive and Sustainable Energy Solutions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme on Inclusive and Sustainable Energy Solutions will be addressed to policy-makers and energy experts from developing countries with a particular focus on participants from LDCs. LDCs urgently need to address their energy gaps, while being mindful not to follow the resource intensive and polluting pathways already taken by most developed countries.  The solutions discussed in the program#s sessions are tailored towards increasing access to electricity, increasing energy security through developing indigenous resources and decreasing dependence on imported fossil fuels, limiting the carbon intensity of energy systems through renewables and efficiency measures, and developing the appropriate business models that would ensure continued operations.  Such systems are already being put in place in several UNIDO projects, examples of which are showcased as global best practices in the session lectures, where actual project experiences are shared for better understanding of realities in the field and in particular country contexts.  It is also explained how south-south cooperation could enable technology transfer, innovation and cost reduction, considering that these are major bottlenecks for LDCs# adoption of clean technologies.  The Program will make use of a dynamic mix of lecture-based and participatory</narrative>
  </description>
